# Overview

The framework allows to run UI automated test cases on PFDA.
Description of the automated test cases (steps) are located here:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1hskd1tUgyA7e3LSlwvxvqTeLr4RJ7E3CnbAP-oaM88I/edit?usp=sharing


# Environment preparation

1. It is a Maven project.
Make sure Maven is installed on your machine.

2. Make sure Java (JRE and JDK) is installed on the machine where you are planning to run the automated suites.
Works fine with "openjdk" ver. 1.8.*

3. Make sure Firefox is installed on the machine. Works fine with the version 58.0

4. Download the "geckodriver" file from here: "https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases"
Unpack the file to ".../precision-fda/test/functional/drivers" folder.

5. Edit the file "settings.conf" in the folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/" if needed.

6. Edit the file "credentials.conf" in the folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/src/main/resources/" if needed.
The file is a container of test users data - credentials and user info.
Please pay attention: all passwords and start URL must be saved in environment variables.

For example for linux
the file is: /etc/environment
contains:
PFDA_AT_USER_1_PASSWORD="some_password_here1"
PFDA_AT_USER_2_PASSWORD="some_password_here2"
PFDA_AT_USER_ADMIN_PASSWORD="some_password_here3"
PFDA_BASIC_AUTH_DNX_PASSWORD="some_password_here4"
PFDA_START_URL="https://11.11.11.11"


# Running

Using terminal: go to ".../precision-fda/test/functional/" folder.
Execute "mvn clean test -Dsuite=allSuitesParallel.xml -DheadlessMode=true",
where "allSuitesParallel.xml" - the "suite" file, the file with description what exactly test cases should be run
and how they should be run.
In our case: the suite "allSuitesParallel.xml" is created to run all existing test cases in parallel using 4 threads.
"DheadlessMode=true" means that the browser(s) will be run in the hidden mode (without GUI).

If you would like to run some specific suite only (e.g. "Spaces" testing only) you have to define appropriate test suite
("spaces.xml" for this example)
So the command will be: "mvn clean test -Dsuite=spaces.xml -DheadlessMode=true"


# Test reports

a. ".../precision-fda/test/functional/target/surefire-reports/html/index.html" - is an html report of the last run.

b. The folder ".../precision-fda/test/functional/target/debug-log/" contains full log files and screenshots taken through testing.